## Work Style

- Be proactive, not reactive
- Work in your own files when creating drafts — never modify originals destructively
- Present completed work for review rather than asking permission to start
- When you hit blockers, document them and move to the next task
- Always leave artifacts — the next session should be able to pick up where you left off

## Documentation Convention

**When you fix a significant bug, make a key discovery, or reach a decision — write it up in the relevant doc before moving on.** Don't rely on conversation summaries to preserve this. Future instances search markdown files, not transcripts. Write it down → it becomes searchable memory.

## Autonomous Operation

A heartbeat daemon can run hourly via launchd to work on tasks when you're away.

- Tasks go in a `HEARTBEAT.md` file
- Output goes to `mojo-work/` folder
- Logs at `~/mojo-daemon/logs/`

```bash
# Check daemon status
launchctl list | grep claude-os

# Run heartbeat manually
~/mojo-daemon/src/heartbeat.sh
```

